18
00:00:12,498 --> 00:00:15,498
http://hiqve.com/

19
00:00:17,522 --> 00:00:19,357
<i>War profiteers!</i>

20
00:00:19,441 --> 00:00:23,445
<i>In time of war, credits are
the fuel that fund all operations.</i>

21
00:00:23,528 --> 00:00:26,489
<i>Senator Amidala is sent to Scipio
to resolve matters</i>

22
00:00:26,573 --> 00:00:30,410
<i>between the Republic
and intergalactic Banking Clan.</i>

23
00:00:30,493 --> 00:00:34,122
<i>Here she is reunited with Rush Clovis,
a once close friend,</i>

24
00:00:34,206 --> 00:00:36,374
<i>but now known traitor to the Republic.</i>

25
00:00:36,458 --> 00:00:39,920
<i>When Clovis reveals corruption
at the core of the Banking Clan,</i>

26
00:00:40,003 --> 00:00:42,756
<i>Senator Amidala
helps him steal vital files</i>

27
00:00:42,839 --> 00:00:45,592
<i>that may uncover
the full extent of the plot.</i>

28
00:00:45,675 --> 00:00:48,470
<i>Anakin Skywalker is sent
to rescue the Senator</i>

29
00:00:48,553 --> 00:00:51,097
<i>and escort the information
back to Coruscant,</i>

30
00:00:51,181 --> 00:00:53,934
<i>leaving the Banking Clan in chaos.</i>

31
00:01:00,148 --> 00:01:03,068
<i>The Jedi Anakin Skywalker
should never have been allowed</i>

32
00:01:03,151 --> 00:01:06,154
<i>to leave with the Senator in tow.</i>

33
00:01:06,238 --> 00:01:10,909
<i>Any future disruptions will be placed
upon your shoulders, Nix Card.</i>

34
00:01:10,992 --> 00:01:12,410
As you wish.

35
00:01:13,828 --> 00:01:17,791
Sir, we have confirmed
that Rush Clovis was on the Jedi's ship.

36
00:01:18,291 --> 00:01:20,585
<i>Then there's nothing we can do.</i>

37
00:01:20,669 --> 00:01:22,545
But they have the files!

38
00:01:22,629 --> 00:01:27,634
<i>Unfortunate, yes, but they need
more than just files to incriminate us.</i>

39
00:01:27,717 --> 00:01:30,720
<i>That will only take them time.</i>

40
00:01:30,804 --> 00:01:32,597
<i>We will all be destroyed.</i>

41
00:01:32,681 --> 00:01:35,433
We must remain calm.

42
00:01:35,517 --> 00:01:37,894
The only way
they could find our secret accounts

43
00:01:37,978 --> 00:01:40,188
is if one of us told them.

44
00:01:40,272 --> 00:01:43,984
<i>I want it noted that you
and you alone allowed this to happen,</i>

45
00:01:44,067 --> 00:01:47,279
and that it has put us all at risk!

46
00:02:08,091 --> 00:02:10,593
<i>You're late! What news?</i>

47
00:02:10,677 --> 00:02:14,180
Clovis, the Senator
and the Jedi are on their way.

48
00:02:14,264 --> 00:02:17,392
<i>-With the information?</i>
-Enough.

49
00:02:17,475 --> 00:02:23,606
<i>Good. Then we can continue
to the next stage of the proceedings.</i>

50
00:02:23,690 --> 00:02:25,525
And what about me?

51
00:02:26,401 --> 00:02:30,196
<i>You will be protected, I can assure you.</i>

52
00:03:10,653 --> 00:03:11,863
Master Yoda?

53
00:03:11,946 --> 00:03:14,532
We weren't expecting
such a formal welcome, Master.

54
00:03:14,616 --> 00:03:18,536
A personal request of the Chancellor's,
my escorting you was, Senator.

55
00:03:18,620 --> 00:03:21,748
Adventures have you had
on Scipio, hmm?

56
00:03:21,831 --> 00:03:26,252
-Have you met Rush Clovis?
-Met we have, yes.

57
00:03:26,336 --> 00:03:29,255
Intrigued we are by your return
to Coruscant.

58
00:03:29,339 --> 00:03:32,092
Much distrust is focused upon you.

59
00:03:32,509 --> 00:03:35,929
I understand, but I hope to right
the wrongs that I have done.

60
00:03:36,721 --> 00:03:38,640
Delay, we must not.

61
00:03:44,729 --> 00:03:48,108
Excuse me
if I find it hard to trust you, Clovis.

62
00:03:48,191 --> 00:03:50,026
You used to sit on this very Senate

63
00:03:50,110 --> 00:03:53,363
even as you funneled credits
into the droid foundries of Count Dooku.

64
00:03:53,446 --> 00:03:57,742
I understand all of your trepidation.
But there is corruption in the banks.

65
00:03:57,826 --> 00:04:00,370
And once we find this corruption?

66
00:04:00,453 --> 00:04:03,498
I believe the ones responsible
should be ousted from control

67
00:04:03,581 --> 00:04:06,251
before the entire
banking infrastructure collapses.

68
00:04:06,334 --> 00:04:08,169
And I suppose you're the man to do it?

69
00:04:08,253 --> 00:04:11,756
I only want the Banking Clan
to be what it once was,

70
00:04:11,840 --> 00:04:14,300
a fair system of trade and commerce.

71
00:04:14,384 --> 00:04:16,302
I came here to root out the criminals

72
00:04:16,386 --> 00:04:18,805
and reveal the truth
behind what is happening.

73
00:04:18,888 --> 00:04:24,060
Now, now, we are grateful
for you bringing us this information,

74
00:04:24,144 --> 00:04:26,855
but what exactly can you prove?

75
00:04:27,605 --> 00:04:31,526
These files show that huge funds
have been diverted out of the banks

76
00:04:31,609 --> 00:04:34,696
and into what I believe
are private accounts.

77
00:04:34,779 --> 00:04:37,157
And the veracity of this information?

78
00:04:37,574 --> 00:04:41,786
I was the one who downloaded the files
from the Muuns' secure mainframe.

79
00:04:41,870 --> 00:04:44,622
I believe that what Clovis is saying
is correct.

80
00:04:44,706 --> 00:04:50,462
Then, Senator Amidala, I would like you
to spearhead this investigation.

81
00:04:50,545 --> 00:04:55,884
Work closely with Rush Clovis and find
and expose these secret accounts.

82
00:04:56,217 --> 00:04:58,761
Once we know exactly
what we are dealing with,

83
00:04:59,888 --> 00:05:05,101
then we can decide
how best to handle this situation.

84
00:05:16,988 --> 00:05:18,573
Why didn't you just say no?

85
00:05:18,656 --> 00:05:20,742
Say no. Why?

86
00:05:21,242 --> 00:05:23,703
I don't want you working with Clovis.

87
00:05:24,037 --> 00:05:26,164
You don't want me working with him?

88
00:05:26,247 --> 00:05:30,210
A serpent can shed its skin,
but it is still a serpent.

89
00:05:30,293 --> 00:05:33,379
Well, you're just going to have
to trust my judgment here.

90
00:05:33,463 --> 00:05:36,716
Like the last time?
When you almost ended up dead?

91
00:05:36,799 --> 00:05:39,886
Or how about you just getting arrested,
and it was me who had to bail you out?

92
00:05:40,428 --> 00:05:43,181
The Chancellor has asked me
to do this, Anakin.

93
00:05:43,264 --> 00:05:47,685
But I am asking you to say no.
As your husband,

94
00:05:47,769 --> 00:05:51,356
I demand that you tell the Chancellor
you are stepping down.

95
00:05:51,439 --> 00:05:54,484
Demand? We've been over this before.

96
00:05:54,567 --> 00:05:58,696
I'm not foolish enough to allow myself
to be deceived twice, Anakin.

97
00:05:58,780 --> 00:06:01,658
My sole intentions are
to defend the Republic.

98
00:06:02,534 --> 00:06:04,702
If you can't trust me...

99
00:06:04,786 --> 00:06:08,498
Excuse the interruption, Padmé.
Shall we begin?

100
00:06:08,581 --> 00:06:11,209
Yes, of course.

101
00:06:11,292 --> 00:06:12,961
General Skywalker.

102
00:06:32,272 --> 00:06:34,274
<i>Darth Tyranus,</i>

103
00:06:34,357 --> 00:06:38,611
<i>it is time for you once again
to recruit our friend Clovis.</i>

104
00:06:39,320 --> 00:06:43,116
<i>He appears to have lost his way.</i>

105
00:06:43,199 --> 00:06:45,702
And how would you like me to do that?

106
00:06:45,785 --> 00:06:49,581
<i>We're going to help him
take over the Banking Clan.</i>

107
00:06:49,664 --> 00:06:52,250
<i>But first, you must entrap him,</i>

108
00:06:52,333 --> 00:06:56,754
<i>so he has no one else to turn to.</i>

109
00:06:56,838 --> 00:07:00,258
Of course, my Lord. As you wish.

110
00:07:09,517 --> 00:07:11,477
I've been looking for you.

111
00:07:11,561 --> 00:07:14,230
-Something wrong?
-You tell me.

112
00:07:15,231 --> 00:07:16,524
Not that I'm aware.

113
00:07:17,400 --> 00:07:21,696
Master Yoda feels that your judgments
concerning Rush Clovis are clouded.

114
00:07:24,365 --> 00:07:26,159
I believe he can't be trusted.

115
00:07:26,242 --> 00:07:28,786
Yes, but there is more, isn't there?

116
00:07:28,870 --> 00:07:32,248
I sense a deep anger in you
by my simply saying his name.

117
00:07:32,707 --> 00:07:36,878
He almost got Senator Amidala killed,
and I would have been responsible.

118
00:07:36,961 --> 00:07:39,631
The Senator has risked her life
many times.

119
00:07:39,714 --> 00:07:42,050
She's quite capable
of taking care of herself.

120
00:07:42,133 --> 00:07:45,053
They had a relationship once.

121
00:07:45,136 --> 00:07:48,848
I simply feel
she's vulnerable to her emotions.

122
00:07:48,931 --> 00:07:51,517
She is, or you?

123
00:07:51,601 --> 00:07:53,811
What are you implying?

124
00:07:53,895 --> 00:07:58,149
Anakin, I understand to a degree
what is going on.

125
00:07:58,232 --> 00:08:02,487
You've met Satine. You know
I once harbored feelings for her.

126
00:08:02,570 --> 00:08:05,948
It's not that we are not allowed
to have these feelings. It's natural.

127
00:08:06,032 --> 00:08:09,535
Senator Amidala and I
are simply friends.

128
00:08:09,619 --> 00:08:11,829
And friends you must remain.

129
00:08:11,913 --> 00:08:16,542
As a Jedi, it is essential you make
the right choice, Anakin, for the Order.

130
00:08:17,460 --> 00:08:19,879
I understand my responsibilities.

131
00:08:21,422 --> 00:08:23,675
Responsibilities that must be observed

132
00:08:23,758 --> 00:08:27,470
whatever relationship develops
between Clovis and Senator Amidala.

133
00:08:27,553 --> 00:08:29,889
They have no relationship.

134
00:08:29,972 --> 00:08:32,600
It is simply business between them.

135
00:08:32,684 --> 00:08:36,062
Then we should have
no problems, should we?

136
00:08:57,375 --> 00:09:01,713
The opera was wonderful, but
I am glad we can get down to business.

137
00:09:02,964 --> 00:09:04,465
If you look here,

138
00:09:04,549 --> 00:09:07,427
the Separatists haven't been repaying
any interest on their loans.

139
00:09:07,510 --> 00:09:11,013
But still the Banking Clan is promising
to lend credits to the Republic.

140
00:09:11,097 --> 00:09:12,682
Credits they simply don't have.

141
00:09:12,765 --> 00:09:14,767
But where have all the savings gone?

142
00:09:14,851 --> 00:09:16,561
Each of the files that you downloaded

143
00:09:16,644 --> 00:09:19,021
shows hundreds and hundreds
of small withdrawals.

144
00:09:19,439 --> 00:09:22,066
Small enough to remain
undetected individually,

145
00:09:22,150 --> 00:09:23,985
but as a sum total,

146
00:09:25,194 --> 00:09:27,238
a devastating theft.

147
00:09:27,321 --> 00:09:31,951
Whoever is behind this is no fool.
We need to find out who's benefiting.

148
00:09:32,034 --> 00:09:34,996
We're still lacking
a critical piece of information.

149
00:09:37,832 --> 00:09:41,627
Whatever we find must remain
between only you and I.

150
00:09:41,711 --> 00:09:43,463
This would be
highly dangerous information

151
00:09:43,546 --> 00:09:47,508
-should it get into the wrong hands.
-Of course.

152
00:09:47,592 --> 00:09:49,427
This reminds me

153
00:09:49,510 --> 00:09:51,929
when we had three nights
to prepare for the Senate hearing

154
00:09:52,013 --> 00:09:56,017
to rescue Bromlarch's
planetary aqueduct system.

155
00:09:56,100 --> 00:09:59,729
And together we saved a people
from total drought and famine.

156
00:09:59,812 --> 00:10:03,024
I don't think either of us
got any sleep that whole week.

157
00:10:03,107 --> 00:10:05,109
Let alone ate anything.

158
00:10:05,860 --> 00:10:08,279
We're not as young as we used to be.

159
00:10:09,989 --> 00:10:12,450
We're not that old either.

160
00:10:12,533 --> 00:10:15,870
You might be right.
Perhaps we should eat something.

161
00:10:18,039 --> 00:10:22,835
So, Clovis, why have you gotten
so involved with the Muuns?

162
00:10:22,919 --> 00:10:25,713
I believe in the banks.
The system works.

163
00:10:25,797 --> 00:10:27,215
The Muuns aren't bad people.

164
00:10:27,298 --> 00:10:28,341
It's just a dishonest few

165
00:10:28,424 --> 00:10:31,469
who are destroying everything
for their own gain.

166
00:10:31,552 --> 00:10:32,887
You know, you've never told me

167
00:10:32,970 --> 00:10:35,473
how you rose to such heights
within the Banking Clan.

168
00:10:35,556 --> 00:10:37,642
It's not a happy story.

169
00:10:37,725 --> 00:10:39,477
My father was personal attaché

170
00:10:39,560 --> 00:10:42,313
to the household
of one of head Muun families.

171
00:10:42,396 --> 00:10:44,148
We were basically servants.

172
00:10:44,232 --> 00:10:46,400
I had no idea.

173
00:10:46,943 --> 00:10:51,447
As I grew up, the head of the family took
a personal interest in my education.

174
00:10:51,531 --> 00:10:55,743
I was the same age as his children,
and so we all studied together.

175
00:10:56,744 --> 00:10:59,580
When my parents and his wife
were killed in a shuttle accident,

176
00:10:59,705 --> 00:11:01,332
he adopted me.

177
00:11:01,415 --> 00:11:04,460
-How old were you?
-Twelve.

178
00:11:04,544 --> 00:11:06,587
That must have been very hard.

179
00:11:06,671 --> 00:11:09,924
I was accepted as their child
everywhere we went.

180
00:11:10,007 --> 00:11:13,761
I almost forgot where I was from
until I looked in the mirror.

181
00:11:13,845 --> 00:11:18,516
-They sound like good people.
-They are. Most Muuns are,

182
00:11:18,599 --> 00:11:22,353
and they want this corruption ended
more than I do.

183
00:11:22,436 --> 00:11:25,565
You should know my contacts
within the Muun government run deep.

184
00:11:25,648 --> 00:11:28,734
I have many allies,
should I need to call on them.

185
00:11:28,818 --> 00:11:32,530
I didn't appreciate
how personal this was for you.

186
00:11:32,613 --> 00:11:36,117
-Now, maybe you will trust me.
-I'm here, aren't I?

187
00:11:36,200 --> 00:11:39,620
I want to thank you
for everything you've done for me.

188
00:11:39,704 --> 00:11:41,914
I don't think I would have had
the strength alone.

189
00:11:41,998 --> 00:11:43,457
Clovis, don't.

190
00:11:44,500 --> 00:11:47,461
-It's that Jedi isn't it?
-General Skywalker?

191
00:11:48,254 --> 00:11:50,214
We're friends, nothing more.

192
00:11:50,298 --> 00:11:53,259
Friends don't argue
the way I saw you arguing today.

193
00:11:54,135 --> 00:11:55,553
You're confused.

194
00:11:55,636 --> 00:11:58,681
Isn't it forbidden
for a Jedi to have romantic ties?

195
00:11:58,764 --> 00:12:00,933
He would be banished from the Order,
would he not?

196
00:12:01,017 --> 00:12:03,769
There is nothing romantic
between he and I.

197
00:12:03,853 --> 00:12:06,731
Then there is absolutely nothing
to stop us from doing this.

198
00:12:06,814 --> 00:12:08,691
Clovis! Clovis, no!

199
00:12:10,318 --> 00:12:11,986
Get away from her!

200
00:12:18,075 --> 00:12:19,702
Anakin ! No!

201
00:12:21,037 --> 00:12:24,665
Why don't you try fighting like a man
without your Jedi tricks?

202
00:12:25,708 --> 00:12:27,376
It would be my pleasure.

203
00:12:32,006 --> 00:12:33,674
Both of you stop this!

204
00:12:33,758 --> 00:12:35,009
You don't have a say in this!

205
00:12:37,136 --> 00:12:39,847
I thought you said
he didn't have feelings for you?

206
00:12:44,060 --> 00:12:46,520
I see you for what you truly are!

207
00:12:53,235 --> 00:12:55,196
You're a serpent, a traitor!

208
00:12:58,824 --> 00:13:01,410
Please! Stop this! No!

209
00:13:02,703 --> 00:13:04,580
Is that all you got?

210
00:13:05,373 --> 00:13:09,251
You should accept that the Senator
has other interests than you.

211
00:13:18,052 --> 00:13:20,429
Skywalker, you fool.

212
00:13:20,513 --> 00:13:24,475
Stop it! Anakin, stop!
What are you doing?

213
00:13:28,521 --> 00:13:29,605
I'm sorry.

214
00:13:29,689 --> 00:13:32,566
<i>Senator Amidala,
is everything okay in there?</i>

215
00:13:32,650 --> 00:13:34,860
No. Come in immediately.

216
00:13:35,277 --> 00:13:36,570
What has happened here?

217
00:13:38,072 --> 00:13:40,157
There was an attack.

218
00:13:40,241 --> 00:13:43,452
It was good fortune
to have General Skywalker here.

219
00:13:43,536 --> 00:13:45,997
They escaped in a speeder
over the balcony.

220
00:13:46,080 --> 00:13:48,290
Is that what happened, sir?

221
00:13:48,374 --> 00:13:50,584
If that's what the man says.

222
00:13:53,212 --> 00:13:54,839
A medic droid is on its way.

223
00:13:54,922 --> 00:13:57,842
Please, help Clovis into the bedroom.

224
00:14:02,972 --> 00:14:04,223
Padmé, I'm...

225
00:14:04,306 --> 00:14:06,767
Stay away from me.

226
00:14:26,120 --> 00:14:29,415
-How is he?
-Nothing that won't heal.

227
00:14:29,498 --> 00:14:32,001
I'm so sorry, Padmé.

228
00:14:32,084 --> 00:14:34,128
I don't know what came over me.

229
00:14:34,211 --> 00:14:36,088
What's done is done.

230
00:14:37,548 --> 00:14:39,759
It's just when I saw you
about to kiss him...

231
00:14:39,842 --> 00:14:42,970
And I regret that,
but it was not what you thought.

232
00:14:43,804 --> 00:14:46,640
And you must know
I don't care for Clovis.

233
00:14:46,724 --> 00:14:48,267
Don't you?

234
00:14:48,350 --> 00:14:53,481
I've told you why I'm doing this,
but still you refuse to accept it.

235
00:14:53,564 --> 00:14:57,401
-You could have killed him, Anakin.
-I know.

236
00:14:57,485 --> 00:15:02,073
This marriage is not a marriage, Anakin,
if there isn't any trust.

237
00:15:02,823 --> 00:15:06,160
We said at the beginning
that this could be a terrible mistake.

238
00:15:06,243 --> 00:15:08,412
What exactly are you saying?

239
00:15:08,496 --> 00:15:12,083
That other people who are married
have everything that we don't,

240
00:15:12,166 --> 00:15:13,626
everything that we won't.

241
00:15:13,709 --> 00:15:15,503
We live in secret, Anakin.

242
00:15:15,586 --> 00:15:20,591
Like it or not, our relationship is built
on lies and deception.

243
00:15:20,674 --> 00:15:22,802
No relationship can survive that.

244
00:15:22,885 --> 00:15:25,763
I know I went too far. It's just...

245
00:15:25,846 --> 00:15:28,265
It's just something inside me snapped.

246
00:15:28,349 --> 00:15:31,060
I don't know who's in there sometimes.

247
00:15:31,143 --> 00:15:35,106
I just know that I'm not happy anymore.
I don't feel safe.

248
00:15:35,189 --> 00:15:37,274
But, Padmé...

249
00:15:37,358 --> 00:15:40,444
I think it's best
if we don't see each other anymore.

250
00:15:40,528 --> 00:15:43,489
At least not for a while.
I'm sorry, Anakin.

251
00:15:46,200 --> 00:15:47,868
I'm sorry, too.

252
00:15:50,287 --> 00:15:52,039
Everything all right, Senator?

253
00:15:53,791 --> 00:15:55,251
No.

254
00:16:17,064 --> 00:16:18,732
Nothing appears to be broken.

255
00:16:19,150 --> 00:16:22,319
But more importantly,
someone wants to speak with you.

256
00:16:22,403 --> 00:16:24,029
What are you talking about?

257
00:16:24,113 --> 00:16:26,824
I am a servant of Count Dooku.

258
00:16:31,871 --> 00:16:34,832
<i>-Hello, Clovis.</i>
-What do you want, Dooku?

259
00:16:34,915 --> 00:16:39,086
<i>It appears we have a mutual problem
that I would like to fix.</i>

260
00:16:39,420 --> 00:16:43,007
I know the Separatists have not been
repaying their loans to the banks.

261
00:16:43,090 --> 00:16:45,843
<i>Now why would we
support corruption?</i>

262
00:16:45,926 --> 00:16:47,052
You expect me to believe

263
00:16:47,136 --> 00:16:50,181
that Lesser and his associates
have no ties with you?

264
00:16:50,264 --> 00:16:53,517
They've allowed you to borrow credits
and not pay any interest.

265
00:16:53,934 --> 00:16:57,855
<i>What you say is correct,
but that information, if made public,</i>

266
00:16:57,938 --> 00:17:01,984
<i>will only bring war to Scipio,
and the banks will fall.</i>

267
00:17:02,067 --> 00:17:03,903
<i>Nobody wants that.</i>

268
00:17:03,986 --> 00:17:05,529
<i>So in the interests of all,</i>

269
00:17:05,613 --> 00:17:08,657
<i>I suggest we come
to some arrangement.</i>

270
00:17:08,741 --> 00:17:10,326
What are you saying?

271
00:17:10,409 --> 00:17:12,786
<i>That the banks need
new management,</i>

272
00:17:12,870 --> 00:17:16,540
<i>and that it could be you.</i>

273
00:17:16,624 --> 00:17:18,542
<i>That I would like help.</i>

274
00:17:18,626 --> 00:17:21,212
If I didn't know better,
I'd say you were afraid.

275
00:17:21,295 --> 00:17:24,131
<i>I prefer the term careful.</i>

276
00:17:25,132 --> 00:17:27,801
<i>These are delicate matters.</i>

277
00:17:27,885 --> 00:17:31,722
<i>We need funds just as the Republic
does to pay for this war.</i>

278
00:17:31,805 --> 00:17:33,933
<i>I can give you the location
of the secret accounts</i>

279
00:17:34,016 --> 00:17:35,059
<i>you are searching for</i>

280
00:17:35,142 --> 00:17:37,811
<i>so you can plead your case
to the Senate.</i>

281
00:17:37,895 --> 00:17:39,813
And you won't stand in my way?

282
00:17:39,897 --> 00:17:43,025
<i>We'll even start paying the interest
on our loans</i>

283
00:17:43,108 --> 00:17:46,445
<i>to show the Republic our
full endorsement.</i>

284
00:17:46,820 --> 00:17:48,781
What do you get out of this?

285
00:17:48,864 --> 00:17:52,493
<i>Stability in unstable times.</i>

286
00:17:52,576 --> 00:17:55,621
<i>The location of the accounts
are on this disk.</i>

287
00:18:00,960 --> 00:18:04,004
Now, where were we?

288
00:18:08,926 --> 00:18:11,387
The Muun government
has seized the accounts

289
00:18:11,470 --> 00:18:14,056
and arrested the heads
of the Banking Clan.

290
00:18:14,139 --> 00:18:18,394
We are indebted to Rush Clovis
for his service to our people.

291
00:18:18,477 --> 00:18:20,938
Well, I have done
only what I thought was right.

292
00:18:21,021 --> 00:18:22,856
Considering the information,

293
00:18:22,940 --> 00:18:25,609
it appears that the Separatist
government has agreed

294
00:18:25,693 --> 00:18:28,779
to allow you
to be the new head of the banks.

295
00:18:28,862 --> 00:18:33,659
-And the Republic?
-I can only give you my endorsement.

296
00:18:34,201 --> 00:18:37,162
Now, all that stands in your way
is the Senate.

297
00:18:42,126 --> 00:18:44,420
<i>Order! Order!</i>

298
00:18:47,881 --> 00:18:50,301
-Good luck.
-Thank you!

299
00:18:50,384 --> 00:18:53,053
<i>Rush Clovis will now
address the Senate.</i>

300
00:18:54,054 --> 00:18:55,389
Traitor!

301
00:18:57,016 --> 00:18:58,392
Clovis?

302
00:18:59,893 --> 00:19:03,480
<i>I come to you today
with irrefutable evidence</i>

303
00:19:03,564 --> 00:19:06,608
<i>that the heads of the Banking Clan
have been stealing funds</i>

304
00:19:06,692 --> 00:19:09,194
<i>and have virtually bankrupted
the system.</i>

305
00:19:09,903 --> 00:19:12,364
-What?
-How dare you!

306
00:19:12,448 --> 00:19:15,743
<i>I know the Muuns to be
a good and honest people,</i>

307
00:19:15,826 --> 00:19:20,706
<i>and that it is the actions of only these
unscrupulous few who are responsible.</i>

308
00:19:20,789 --> 00:19:24,626
<i>I humbly ask you for your nomination
in taking over the banks.</i>

309
00:19:24,710 --> 00:19:25,961
What can you do?

310
00:19:26,045 --> 00:19:27,504
<i>I will restore order</i>

311
00:19:27,588 --> 00:19:31,216
<i>and return the banks back to secure
and neutral negotiations</i>

312
00:19:31,300 --> 00:19:32,343
<i>and transactions.</i>

313
00:19:32,426 --> 00:19:34,303
How can we trust you?

314
00:19:34,386 --> 00:19:35,846
<i>I vow to be impartial</i>

315
00:19:35,929 --> 00:19:38,849
<i>and show no favor
to either side in this war.</i>

316
00:19:38,932 --> 00:19:41,435
But you have colluded
with the Separatists!

317
00:19:42,394 --> 00:19:44,313
<i>It is the Separatists' ties to Rush Clovis</i>

318
00:19:44,396 --> 00:19:47,274
<i>that has allowed them
to accept this nomination.</i>

319
00:19:47,358 --> 00:19:51,528
<i>He also has the full support
of the Muun people.</i>

320
00:19:51,612 --> 00:19:54,114
<i>And what of the Chancellor?</i>

321
00:19:54,698 --> 00:19:58,035
<i>I believe that in these dangerous times,</i>

322
00:19:58,118 --> 00:20:01,205
<i>the bank must be protected at all costs,</i>

323
00:20:01,288 --> 00:20:04,875
<i>and that a man
who has no allegiance to either side</i>

324
00:20:04,958 --> 00:20:09,254
<i>and the support of the Muun people
is our best hope.</i>

325
00:20:09,338 --> 00:20:11,423
<i>Then we shall put it to a vote.</i>

326
00:20:23,268 --> 00:20:27,272
<i>A resounding majority
in support of the nomination.</i>

327
00:20:45,874 --> 00:20:49,545
My boy, I can tell
this has been a difficult time.

328
00:20:49,628 --> 00:20:53,507
I've known you too long
not to see something is troubling you.

329
00:20:53,590 --> 00:20:55,426
Your Excellency, forgive me,

330
00:20:55,509 --> 00:20:59,263
but you have made a mistake
by trusting Clovis.

331
00:20:59,346 --> 00:21:00,514
Have I?

332
00:21:00,597 --> 00:21:04,101
Rest assured,
my public endorsement of Clovis

333
00:21:04,184 --> 00:21:07,771
is not the same
as my private confidence in him.

334
00:21:07,855 --> 00:21:10,232
Then what exactly is going on here?

335
00:21:10,315 --> 00:21:12,776
We will watch him closely.

336
00:21:12,860 --> 00:21:15,446
I don't dispute your distrust of him.

337
00:21:15,529 --> 00:21:18,907
I think there is something
we haven't unearthed yet,

338
00:21:18,991 --> 00:21:21,785
and I would very much like
for it to surface.

339
00:21:21,869 --> 00:21:26,165
But people have been hurt,
could be hurt, in the process.

340
00:21:26,582 --> 00:21:29,334
Let us make sure that doesn't happen,
shall we?

341
00:21:29,334 --> 00:21:30,377
Let us make sure that doesn't happen,
shall we?

342
00:21:30,401 --> 00:21:35,401
http://hiqve.com/

